Bring a large #saucepan{} of water with @salt{1/2%tsp} to the boil on high heat.

Quarter the @salad potatoes{350%grams} (no need to peel).

When your pan of water is boiling, add the potatoes and simmer until you can
easily slip a knife through, ~{15-20%minutes}.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of @oil{drizzle} in a large #frying pan{} on
medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the @diced British chicken breast{260%grams} to the pan and season
with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Fry until golden brown on the outside and cooked through, ~{8-10%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging.
> It's cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

While everything cooks, peel and grate the @garlic clove{1} (or use a
#garlic press{}).

Boil a half-full #kettle{} for the dressing.

Crush the @cashew nuts{40%grams} in the unopened sachet using a #rolling pin{}.

Halve the @cherry tomatoes{125%grams}.

Halve the @lime{1}.

Meanwhile, add the @peanut butter{30%grams} and @boiled water{2%tbsp} for the
dressing into a large #bowl{} and mix until it makes a smooth paste.

Stir in the @sweet chilli sauce{32%grams} and squeeze all the lime juice into
your bowl of dressing.

Combine well to make a smooth dressing. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Once the chicken is cooked, add the @Indonesian style spice mix{1%sachet} and
garlic to the pan, stir-fry for ~{1%minute}.

Once the potatoes are ready, drain in a #colander{}, then add to the chicken.

Next, stir in the @honey{1%tbsp}. Toss the chicken and potatoes until evenly
coated and remove from the heat. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

When everything's ready, add the @baby leaf mix{50%grams}, tomatoes, and cooked
chicken and potatoes to your bowl of peanut dressing.

Toss together and share between your serving bowls.

Taste and season with @salt{} and @pepper{} if needed. Sprinkle over the
cashews to finish. Enjoy!